{
  "texts": [
    "RL uses learning control policies to solve the problem by optimizing reward signals.",
    "Nevertheless, QL is used to estimate the value of actions by a maximization step that tends to overvalue rather than undervalue.",
    "In this overestimation problem, the agent chooses non-optimal operations for any state due to the large Q values of the agent.",
    "The RL algorithm updates the program according to the rewards and observations obtained from the environment to maximize the expected long-term reward [13].",
    "RL is a modelization of how human beings learn by acting on the current state of the environment and obtaining rewards."
  ]
}